I frequently visit the one in Prentice Women's Hospital in Chicago.  These people FREQUENTLY get my order wrong, or the coffee is watery even after a shot of expresso, or they have given me the wrong food.  Today, the store lead looks at me like she is crazy with her confrontational stance, because she had a new girl working on my drink that I ended up bringing back down.  She did not really want to listen, and had serious attitude, so I will contact corporate on Monday.  I spend $7-10 whenever I do order from there.  Why is the staff pissed because you return food or drinks that THEY have screwed up?  Why?  I am paying for it, aren't I?  Am I PAYING YOU for what I want? The coffee at this Dunkin Donuts location taste awful.  As an major Dunkin Donut consumer I was so happy when they place this location in the building. The convenience is absolutely great for my morning fix.  When they first opened the coffee was great and I became a loyal every morning customer. However now it has begun to taste as if their filters are never cleaned and despite adding tons of sugared flavor and cream the coffee still has a horrible bitter taste.  Some mornings I even have coffee grounds in the bottom of my cup. Yuck!  I have complained to management and even tried to give this location extra chances due to its convenience. But the coffee is gross and I'm beginning to feel as though I waste my money every morning.  If this was the first location I had ever tried Dunkin Donuts coffee.. I would believe that Dunkin Donuts had horrible coffee and would never try one again. Luckily I know that its just this location.  I gave it 2 stars because the staff is friendly enough and I hate giving their location a bad review but the coffee really is horrible.  Hopefully this can be fixed.
